”Well, guess what, at least you can’t break me anymore” [ Loki x Stark!Reader x Lizzie Stark ] P.1?

Summary: when Loki had invaded the earth and S.H.I.E.L.D had taken him, y/n decided to talk to him of why he’s here.

A/N: Yay, another one shot of this family. I don’t know if I should do another part, what do you guys think? Leave a comment!

Warnings; sad, angst, manipulation, and grammar.

———————

You walked into the small ’prison’ was Loki was held. Ever since he had walked into the earth and was a threat to the human kind the superheroes wanted to stop him and find out why he did this.

That’s why you were into it, without your father’s knowledge and your sister. Of course, she could know when something was wrong with you because of the ’twin power you had’

You walked towards the small room where you saw Loki’s back on you with his hands. ”Well, well, here is the famous Stark Twin, y/n Stark,” he told you as he grinned at turned around.

”Well, what do I have the honor to meet you?” He asked which you made roll your eyes. ”Does your father knows that you’re here?”

”No, and I would like to keep this way,” you told him as you glared. Loki just kept staring you with mischief on his face. You wanted to know why he was here because of none of the Avengers knew why.

Nat would of course know because of her skills but, seeing that she was in a heating argument with your father, that was the chance you had to sneak out. Lizzie was just too into the argument along with Tony.

” I want you to tell me why are you doing this and what do you want from us, ” you demanded him.

”Everyone wants something, right? That’s why you and I are so alike, ” he told you as he pointed at you.

”What do you mean?” you furrowed your eyebrows in confusion. ”Y/N Stark, a teenage girl with many issues, and struggling to fit in the family and sometimes wondering that she doesn’t belong there, ” he continued to say.

You know that it was true, every word he told you. Sometimes when you saw your father and Lizzie always laughing and had his great relationships between father and daughter, made you jealous.

It made you think differently because you were different than Tony and Lizzie. Lizzie was this pretty, popular and smart girl while where you were just, a girl who overthinks much.

You looked at Loki and he was grinning, he knew that he was right. ”we’re nothing alike, ” you began to say which made him chuckle. ”Oh, please, is the second child in the family? And the father is having their favorite daughter leaving you just an outcast,”

”Admit it, you’re just a broken girl with many issues,” he mocked you. Tears begin to come down as you held your hands tightly into your fist.

”Well, guess what, at least you can’t break me anymore,” you told him as you raised your right hand against him as you saw him scream in pain.

His hands were on his head as he screamed so painfully. This was something positive with your power that you could do a powerful migraine just through supernatural.

You broke off by your powers as you heard him laughing. You looked at him in confusion and then at your hand. ”Why didn’t it work?” You asked him as the tears were on your cheeks.

”Well, it because I’m a god your silly girl and those powers don’t work on me but, on others well, they work perfectly,”

”What do you mean?”

”This was my plan along, to have some of the Stark Twins to follow my lead and bring chaos to the people who call the Avengers,”

And by those words, you leashed out of your powers in anger which made the electricity gone wild.

-

Lizzie was stood in a circle as she watched when the others argued. She suddenly felt something and she knew that y/n was in danger. It wasn’t because of the twin power they had but it was also she could see the lamps in the room, flickering violently.

And with that, because she was the only one who had paid attention, she looked around and she saw that the door was open and she knew that you were gone to see off Loki.

”Shut up! This isn’t going to help anyone if everybody was arguing each other!” Lizzie screamed that made everyone looked at her.

Tony looked at Lizzie’s horrified look by on her face. ”What’s wrong?” He asked her.

”Y/n,” she began to say as she ran out of the room and ignored her father calls and the others. Lizzie ran where Loki was captured as saw that the glass around his ’prison’ was completely shattered and that y/n was gone. Along with Loki.

”She’s gone,” Lizzie gasped and told them as everyone watched.

”And she disappeared with Loki,” Natasha said as she glanced at Tony.

”what does he want with her?” Tony asked for everyone in the group.

”I don’t know but, I know one thing and that’s Loki only want her powers because she’s the most powerful than me, ”

body:
SPOILERS: Thor in Endgame

Contrary to some other opinions, I think Thor had a great role in Endgame. Not only was he a funny comic relief, he also majorly kicked Thanos’ ass during the climax even with all his hobo hair and beer belly.

But in a way it’s kinda sad. He felt so responsible for not being able to kill Thanos that he turned to alcohol and Fortnite just to drown out the guilt.

And the way the other Avengers handled it was really sweet too. Bruce never belittled Thor for turning fat and being constantly drunk. Bruce understood that Thor has had a tough few years and asking him to fight Thanos again was a huge favor.

None of the Avengers blamed him either. Even if Thor looks really goofy now, they know that he’s just as devastated as the rest of them and doing his best to supress it (under a couple barrels of Asgardian Booze).

So when he went to put on the gauntlet, Tony gently stopped him and was basically all “Thor I know how much you want to do this but you’re not really in the best shape buddy”.

Idk it was something i wanted to talk about

Also did anyone notice how Thor’s beard turned into this dope braid when he summons his armor??? Marvel legit gave him a magical girl transformation and i just

summary:
I want to tell you a story. 
So when I was 7 years old my older brother (he was 21 when this happened) took me to cinema to see...
body:
I want to tell you a story.

So when I was 7 years old my older brother (he was 21 when this happened) took me to cinema to see Iron Man. I fell in love hard. Not like I had a crush on Tony Stark or something. It was just fangirl love. Then he showed me some more Marvel movies when they came out. I became a huge fan back then.

When my mum decided that I’m old enough to go to the cinema only with my friends (I was 11) , we went to see The Avengers. I fell even more.

Right now my adventure with mcu is 11 years old. Yesterday I saw Avengers: Endgame with the same brother that took me to the cinema to see Iron Man.

We started this together and we ended it together.

I wanted to thank not only my brother but every person that took part in creating mcu. They gave me my best years of childhood and teenage years. I love you 3000 ❤

PS. By the way that was my first time ever at cinema and I am so grateful that it happend to be Iron Man movie

summary: So there’s canonically a year that Loki spent in the void/clutches of thanos and I started thinking about how goddamn impressive...
body:
So there’s canonically a year that Loki spent in the void/clutches of thanos and I started thinking about how goddamn impressive it is that Loki held out that long before he could be “persuaded” to go to Midgard for the tessaract. And then it wouldn’t leave me alone so I wrote a Drabble whoops.

Loki. Amongst Thanos’ soldiers, the name was enough to instantly inspire throughout their ranks a feeling of grudging respect, reluctant admiration, and no small amount of fear, if they were being completely honest. He was legendary among the mad titan’s armies for his ability to withstand their most creative and brutal tortures. It had taken them over a year to break him, which was an unprecedented record amongst torturers so skillful and vindictive as they were. Even then, he hadn’t agreed to do their bidding of his own free will, and the torture had only served to make him weak enough that the mind stone was actually effective in bringing him under their master’s control. Loki had managed to withstand and repel the power of an infinity stone for over a year. And in the part of their minds where they kept their deepest, darkest secrets, Thanos’ soldiers were afraid of Loki. So afraid, in fact, that at times they had gone too far, to the point where the Asgardian’s heart had stopped beating and they were sure this was the end for them, having killed Thanos’ prized asset (the ability to Skywalk wasn’t something found every day, after all, and was highly necessary for Thanos’ plans to retrieve the tesseract). But he never stayed down, no matter how far they went with their fire and their whips and their weapons of all sorts, and while the fact that he wouldn’t stay dead was a relief (as it meant that they hadn’t accidentally broken their master’s new toy beyond repair) it terrified them a little more every time it happened.

Once they’d finally carried out their mission and Loki was under the control of Thanos and his Lieutenant, known only as The Other, they thought that surely he would not last a week after carrying out his great mission. But he’d surprised them all, even Thanos, by not only subverting the control of the mind stone enough to fail, but breaking it completely with nothing more than an (albeit fairly intense) blow to the head. It shouldn’t have been possible. Nothing that Loki did should have been possible. And so they feared him, even under their sneers and jibes and taunts in his direction as they tortured him, and even afterwards, they would look warily around the room as if to ensure he wasn’t somehow watching before they began to talk of him.

Although his children and his soldiers would never acknowledge it, he was sometimes far too arrogant for his own good, and as they watched him supposedly choke Loki to death after receiving the tesseract during their attack on the Asgardian Statesman, they could not help but fear that something wasn’t right with the way their greatest foe had gone down so easily and without circumstance. The fear prickled in the backs of their minds and they spoke of it in hushed tones when they were alone, free from the fear of being overheard by a superior officer who would no doubt discipline them severely for doubting their master.

As it turns out, they were right to worry.

title: Natasha
body:
[SPOILER ALERT]

Now that more people have watched endgame I’m putting my thoughts here about Natasha Romanoff. 

Honestly disappointed at the fact that not enough recognition was made towards this hero. 

She was there from the beginning with all of the avengers and despite having no superpowers she fought all the way through. She was always unselfish and would do anything for her family, especially Cap. 5 years in between IW and endgame she stayed with the hope of finding Hawkeye and keeping all shits together. She sacrificed her life for the universe to be saved. 

What did she get? A shed of tear and a bench tossed across the lake. Having no funeral was already bad enough but not even a single verbal recognition? No praise or appreciation for what she had done this time and over the years? smh this character is done dirty and is always under appreciated

summary:
Thank you Bruce Banner,
For defying the world when it told you you were an enormous green rage monster by proving them wrong as...
body:
sappy feels (after watching endgame)

Thank you Bruce Banner,

For defying the world when it told you you were an enormous green rage monster by proving them wrong as a 7PHD holding and compassionate man.

Thank you Thor,

For reminding me to be perseverant in the face of failure, and to not harden my heart against forgiveness (even if you’re tricked you into believing they died…multiple times).

Thank you Clint Barton,

For showing me that anyone can be a superhero because though you may not be a super soldier or a Norse god, you are just as much of an avenger.

Thank you Natasha Romanoff,

For inspiring me to believe in my own badassery, and take ownership of whatever my own ‘special skillset’ might be.

You will not be forgotten. You will be missed.

Thank you Steve Rogers,

For teaching me to be brave and to always believe in myself, even when the world feels like its crashing down.

Thank you Tony Stark,

For introducing us to this wacky world of superheroes, for proving that people can grow, and for showing everyone what sacrifice truly means.

Thank you for saving us all.

You will not be forgotten. You will be missed.

Love you, 3000.

It’s the end of an era, and all I can say is thank you to the universe for letting me be alive at the same time as this phenomenon.

For defying the world when it told you you were an enormous green rage monster by proving them wrong as a 7PHD holding and compassionate man.

Thank you Thor,

For reminding me to be perseverant in the face of failure, and to not harden my heart against forgiveness (even if you’re tricked you into believing they died…multiple times).

Thank you Clint Barton,

For showing me that anyone can be a superhero because though you may not be a super soldier or a Norse god, you are just as much of an avenger.

Thank you Natasha Romanoff,

For inspiring me to believe in my own badassery, and take ownership of whatever my own ‘special skillset’ might be.

You will not be forgotten. You will be missed.

Thank you Steve Rogers,

For teaching me to be brave and to always believe in myself, even when the world feels like its crashing down.

Thank you Tony Stark,

For introducing us to this wacky world of superheroes, for proving that people can grow, and for showing everyone what sacrifice truly means.

Thank you for saving us all.

You will not be forgotten. You will be missed.

Love you, 3000.

It’s the end of an era, and all I can say is thank you to the universe for letting me be alive at the same time as this phenomenon.

summary: SPOILERS AHEAD, READ AT YOUR OWN RISK
body:
SPOILERS AHEAD, READ AT YOUR OWN RISK

.

.

.

.

Okay, so, to everyone who has a problem with Thor in this movie I just want you to realize a few things.

Thor lost literally everything. His mother, father, brother, most of his if not all of his people, his girlfriend, his best friends, his eye, his home, trust me the list goes on. All I’m saying is, what else has he got? Some powers and a grief strikes heart.

He didn’t just give up. Did you even watch IW? He did his best, and sometimes your best doesn’t cut it but he tried and he gave it his all, and it didn’t work. Even after everything he tried with all those deaths and losses in mind probably weighing down on him, he still lost.

Now think about all that. All that swirling around in his head for five years. All that guilt, anger, sadness, the realization that he couldn’t do the one thing he had left. To avenge those he lost.

That would depress anyone. Man or god. And we’ve all learned Thor is more man than god at this point.

Depression often (at least for me) leads to heavy dissociation, I don’t want to get up. I don’t want to work or feel or do anything. I just want to do everything to try and forget. Pretend like its not happening. I wont take care of myself and sometimes I’ll binge eat because of stress.

Group all that into one and you’ve got and man who’s lost everyone and everything that was ever important to him, who was at the top and beaten down as low as he could go and who couldn’t do anything about it, and because of it went into a depressive dissociation to do the one thing he had left FORGET. If you don’t believe me, look at how hard he gripped Bruce’s arm at the mere mention of Thanos’ name. Begging Bruce not to mention. He wants so badly for all of it to go away.

If you can’t sympathize with him or even try and understand why he behaves the way he does after that, then idk what to tell you.

TLDR: In this house we stan Thor because he was a happy, strong, brave beautiful sweetheart who the universe decided to beat down until we could nearly recognize him.
